  "text": "Meningitis poses additional challenges in treatment. Liposomal amphotericin B for 4-6 weeks followed by itraconazole for at least one year is recommended. Evidence suggests selection of agents that penetrate the CSF is unnecessary. [CITATION_1] An experimental model of Histoplasma meningitis in mice showed that fluconazole, which penetrates CSF well, was less effective than itraconazole or amphotericin B, drugs that do not penetrate CSF. [CITATION_2] Penetration of brain and meninges may be more important than penetration of CSF.",
